# Frontend design (project-local)

When the open workspace contains **`.cursor/skills/impeccable/`**:

1. Read **`PRODUCT.md`** and **`DESIGN.md`** at the project root before UI edits (run **`/impeccable init`** if missing).
2. Prefer **`/impeccable`** commands for design, critique, audit, polish, typeset — not generic "make it prettier" prose.
3. Follow **`.cursor/rules/frontend-design-lane.mdc`** when present.
4. Use **`.cursor/design-refs/README.md`** for inspiration — one reference lane per task.

## Hybrid repos (UI + WebGL)

If **`.cursor/skills/r3f-three/`** is also installed:

- **2D surfaces** (`app/`, `components/`, Tailwind) → this rule + Impeccable.
- **3D surfaces** (`scenes/`, `*Scene*.tsx`, R3F imports) → **`3d-interactive-lane.mdc`** + r3f-three skill. Do not `/impeccable polish` WebGL files.
- See [HYBRID.md](https://github.com/darkyzowo/cursor-agent-stack/blob/master/docs/HYBRID.md).

If Impeccable is not installed, this rule is inert. Install: [docs/FRONTEND.md](https://github.com/darkyzowo/cursor-agent-stack/blob/master/docs/FRONTEND.md).

Do not duplicate checkpoint hooks in project `.cursor/hooks.json` — session memory hooks live in global `~/.cursor/hooks.json`.
